-- Canada Police to Announce Terrorism-Related Arrests Today
-- B y   G r e g   Q u i n n
-- 2013-04-22T18:30:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-22/canada-police-to-announce-terrorism-related-arrests-today.html
Canadian police said they will hold
a press conference to discuss a “national security criminal
investigation” at 3:30 p.m. in Toronto. Police will say there
have been terrorism-related arrests, according to the prime
minister’s office.  The press conference was announced by the  Royal Canadian
Mounted Police . Carl Vallee, spokesman for Prime Minister
 Stephen Harper , confirmed by e-mail terrorism related arrests
will be announced.  The Canadian Broadcasting Corp. reported earlier that there
is no connection to the attack in Boston last week, citing
unnamed security officials. A call to the RCMP wasn’t
immediately returned.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Greg Quinn in Ottawa at 
 gquinn1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
